data.description: Discover your dream home that has been immaculately maintained and priced to impress. This home stands out as the only home with direct access to the Harris Chain of Lakes under 500K. Experience the tranquility of "Old Florida" living in this peaceful waterfront setting. Your backyard canal, complete with seawall, boat lift and screened room with brick pavers and electricity, provides convenient access to the Ocklawaha river within minutes. (This improvement completed by the current owner in 2020) Marvel at the river view from your dock, offering miles of navigable water to the Harris Chain of Lakes.   A comprehensive remodel completed in 2019 ensures modern comfort and style, featuring a new roof, A/C, flooring, paint, updated lighting and granite counter tops. The current owner elevated the living experience by converting appliances to gas, including a tankless hot water heater, dryer, stove (double oven) and fireplace. Also new is the Bosch dishwasher and garbage disposal.    A propane gas tank - 500 gallon - ingeniously sunk in the front yard with access to this from the front shed, fuels these upgrades.  Conveniently located within minutes away from The Villages with every amenity imaginable.   This home boasts a sprawling open floor plan, stunning entertaining kitchen with ample cabinet space, a walk in pantry, and a bonus room  that would make a great office, den or sun room. The large inside laundry room and custom window treatments enhance functionality and style. The french doors lead to a screened patio and have built in blinds. Keyless entry installed on 3 doors. Storm doors at the front and rear entry. Comprehensive security system with cameras in front, back and side. Keypad by the front door. Partially fenced for privacy, this property also features a Generac whole-home generator (16W propane) and two additional sheds for storage.   Custom shoe racks in the 2nd bedroom add a thoughtful touch ready to be removed if requested to do so. Very nicely done if you choose to keep them. This home is truly remarkable - schedule a visit to fully appreciate everything it has to offer. *** Make sure to click on the virtual tour***
